messages.content: Tell me about this dandiset. *

This Dandiset, [DANDI:001433/draft – Breathing rhythm and place dataset](https://dandiarchive.org/dandiset/001433/draft), contains behavioral and electrophysiological data from recordings of sniffing, video, and olfactory bulb (OB) electrophysiology in freely-behaving mice. The animals were not given stimuli, rewards, or tasks. The dataset was generated as part of research supported by the NIH (award 1 R01 NS 123903-03) and curated by Matt Smear.

Key details:

- Species: Mus musculus (house mouse)
- Techniques: Multi-electrode extracellular electrophysiology, behavioral monitoring, and video recording
- Standards: Neurodata Without Borders (NWB)
- Files: 27 NWB files (approx. 41.4 GB)
- Subjects: Data from 4 mice
- Variables measured: Processing modules, electrical series (ephys), and electrode groups

This dataset provides resources to analyze the relationship between breathing rhythm and spatial behavior in mice, focusing on freely-behaving conditions with no imposed tasks. If you would like further details about the files or content, feel free to ask!
